sentences.text:
{{main|Elections in India}}
 announced the schedule for the elections on 16 March 2024.]]
Article 83 of the Constitution of India requires elections to the Lok Sabha to be held once every five years. The 543 Member of Parliament, Lok Sabha|MPs are elected from single-member constituencies using first-past-the-post voting. The One Hundred and Fourth Amendment of the Constitution of India|104th amendment to the Constitution of India|constitution abolished the Anglo-Indian reserved seats in the Lok Sabha|two seats that were reserved for the Anglo-Indian community.

